        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "In {{Zend::loadClass()}} there is a call to {{self::loadFile($file, $dirs, true)}} which instructs the file containing the class to be loaded.  It is not necessary to have the {{true}} as a parameter because at the beginning of the loadClass method there is already a check:\n{code}\nif (class_exists($class, false)) {\n    return;\n}\n{code}\nwhich would halt execution and avoid loading the file twice.\n\nThe other tweak is here on the second comparison operator:\n{code}\nif ($dirs === null && $path != $class) {\n{code}\nsimply a change from {{\\!=}} to {{\\!==}}"
        },
